UNITED STATES, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. James J. QUINLIVIAN, Defendant-Appellant. No. 297. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 2, 1932. Sidney S. Meyers and James D. C. Murray, both of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Thomas E. Dewey and Barent Ten Eyek, Asst. U. S. Attys., both of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court.
